race.comment: CROYDON (6) sizzled around 450m in 25.05 when winning a Grade 4/5 at Warrnambool last start. Has the ability and looks hard to top. PAW TABITHA (1) goes very well at the course with two wins and a placing from four starts. Recorded a nose win (25.49) in a Grade 5 last time at Warrnambool. Looks a key chance on best figures. PAW LEON (2) flew the lids from the middle with a slick turn of foot and stuck on well despite missing the frame, finishing fourth over 450m Ballarat in 25.40. Boasts a strong record from this draw with four wins and three minor placings from 10 starts. Likely to be thereabouts. Something for the Multiples: JOLLY OLD MAC (7)
